cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR 

The paper proposes a camera-based deep neural network method for 3D lane detection with uncertainty estimation. This involves computer vision (CV) techniques for lane detection, robotics (RO) for autonomous driving applications, machine learning (LG) for the deep feature embedding and uncertainty estimation, artificial intelligence (AI) for the overall approach, and cryptography (CR) for the uncertainty estimation calibration. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV, followed by cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.CR.
